\chapter{Bug Report and Fix}
% ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

\section{Problem Statement}

Entering the expression \texttt{18 - 2 =} caused the LCD to display \texttt{18-2=} on line 1 and show \emph{nothing} on line 2 --- the result \texttt{16} was never printed.

\section{Root Cause Analysis}

\begin{warnbox}[Root Cause: Tokeniser in \texttt{pars.c}]
The tokenisation loop read one character at a time. When it encountered \texttt{'1'} followed by \texttt{'8'}, it treated them as two \emph{separate} single-digit tokens instead of the number \texttt{18}. The resulting malformed postfix queue caused the RPN evaluator to produce no valid result.
\end{warnbox}

\textbf{Before fix} --- incorrect token stream:

